title: Asbestos regulations for your commercial property

heading_context: Asbestos regulations for your commercial property
chunks.html_content: If you’re the landlord, tenant or managing agent of a commercial property you may be responsible for managing asbestos, unless your contract or lease says otherwise.
chunks.plain_content:
Asbestos regulations for your commercial property
If you’re the landlord, tenant or managing agent of a commercial property you may be responsible for managing asbestos, unless your contract or lease says otherwise.

heading_context: Asbestos regulations for your commercial property
chunks.html_content:
1. If you have a lease or contract, check who is responsible for asbestos.

  2. Find out where the asbestos is (you’ll probably need an external accredited surveyor to carry out an asbestos survey).

  3. Have the material analysed and keep a record of what you find.

  4. Carry out a health and safety risk assessment.

  5. Share the information with anyone likely to come into contact with the area, such as builders.

  6. Keep anything containing asbestos in good repair or have it sealed or removed.
chunks.plain_content:
Asbestos regulations for your commercial property
What you must do


If you have a lease or contract, check who is responsible for asbestos.


Find out where the asbestos is (you’ll probably need an external accredited surveyor to carry out an asbestos survey).


Have the material analysed and keep a record of what you find.


Carry out a health and safety risk assessment.


Share the information with anyone likely to come into contact with the area, such as builders.


Keep anything containing asbestos in good repair or have it sealed or removed.

heading_context: Asbestos regulations for your commercial property
chunks.html_content: The United Kingdom Accreditation Service (UKAS) will help you find an accredited surveyor and testing laboratory.
chunks.plain_content:

The United Kingdom Accreditation Service (UKAS) will help you find an accredited surveyor and testing laboratory.

heading_context: Asbestos regulations for your commercial property
chunks.html_content:
If you do not have a plan to deal with asbestos and put it in action, you could face:

  • a fine of up to £20,000
  • imprisonment for up to 12 months

For a serious breach you could face an unlimited fine and/or imprisonment of up to 2 years.
